<event name="PIRATE_MANTIS_CHOICE" unique="true">
	<text>You find a Hive Mantis and a pirate ship battling each other. They both seem to recognize a threat in you. Either way, a battle is inevitable, but which do you engage head on?</text>
	<choice>
		<text>Attack the Mantis.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You attack the Mantis head on, weapons blazing. Your attack doesn't faze them, but the pirate takes the chance to flee.</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_MANTIS_GENERIC" hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text>Attack the pirate.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You engage the pirate, firing all you have towards them. Your show of aggression works, and the Mantis hurry away to find an easier fight.</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_PIRATE_ALL" hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice req="FLARE_DISTRACTION">
		<text>(Flares) Launch a flare and get away.</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
	<choice req="cloaking">
		<text>(Cloaking) Cloak and fly away.</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
	<choice req="engines" lvl="5">
		<text>(Upg. Engines) Fly away.</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="AUTO_CHOICE" unique="true">
	<text>An automated satellite rests nearby, with an Auto-guard protecting it. The satellite spots you and alerts the guard.</text>
	<choice>
		<text>Destroy the guard.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You prepare to attack the guard, knowing the satellite will be helpless against you without protection.</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_AUTO_GUARD_CHOICE" hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text>Avoid the guard and destroy the station.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You slip past the guard ship and move to attack the satellite. It appears the guard is programmed to not go within a certain distance of the satellite and is unable to chase you.</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_AUTO_STATION_CHOICE" hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice req="FLARE_DISTRACTION">
		<text>(Flares) Launch a flare and get away.</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
	<choice req="cloaking">
		<text>(Cloaking) Cloak and fly away.</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
	<choice req="engines" lvl="5">
		<text>(Upg. Engines) Fly away.</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
</event>
<eventList name="AUTO_CHOICE_FIGHT_WIN">
	<event>
		<text>With the guard dead, you can easily fire on the station from a distance and take it down. You scrap the remains of both ships.</text>
		<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>You attempt to fire on the satellite, but it is better protected than expected. You cannot get through its defenses, so you move on after scrapping the guard.</text>
		<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
	</event>
</eventList>
<event name="AUTO_CHOICE_SNEAK_WIN">
	<text>With the station disabled, the guard deactivates. You scrap both ships.</text>
	<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
</event>

<event name="INFORMANT_RUNNER" unique="true">
	<text>"Oh good heavens, that's a Federation Renegade! If we turn their location to the Rebels, we'll be rich! Wait, did I just say that on open coms?" The nearby civilian ship mutes themselves, then immediately activates their engines!</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_CIVILIAN_INFORMANT" hostile="false"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Attack, we can't let them escape!</text>
		<event>
			<text>You can't let this information get out!</text>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="MORALITY_UPDATE_GENERAL_FIGHT"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Try to reason with them.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"The Federation is outdated in its philosophies! The Rebellion will offer us a glorious galaxy... nay, Multiverse free from xeno scum!"</text>
			<choice req="LIST_CREW_ENGINEER" hidden="true">
				<text>(Engineer Crew) Persuade them further.</text>
				<event>
					<text>Your Engineer knows what it's like to have been a Rebel, and they reveal the truths of the Rebellion's brutality and hypocrisy to the civilians. They're so taken-aback by this knowledge they even offer supplies towards your cause.</text>
					<autoReward level="LOW">standard</autoReward>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice req="LIST_CREW_JERRY" hidden="true">
				<text>(Jerry) Persuade them further.</text>
				<event>
					<text>Jerry knows what it's like to have been a Rebel, and he reveals the truths of the Rebellion's brutality and hypocrisy to the civilians. They're so taken-aback by this knowledge they even offer supplies towards your cause.</text>
					<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Then you leave us no choice but to silence you.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You tried to reason with the civilians, but you've failed. The only option now is to kill them before they can escape!</text>
					<ship hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice req="weapons" lvl="5" hidden="true">
		<text>(Upg. Weapons) Threaten them.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Alright, alright! You've made your point... and ours. This is why the Federation will fall, because when things go south, all you savages know is to use your guns!"</text>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice req="mind" hidden="true" lvl="1" max_lvl="1">
		<text>(Mind Control) Change their mind.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Your mind control won't last long enough to change their opinion of the Federation entirely, so instead you persuade them that informing the Rebels might put them in more danger than it's worth. Satisfied, you leave the civilians behind.</text>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice req="mind" hidden="true" lvl="2">
		<text>(Upg. Mind Control) Change their mind.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"You know what, I've changed my mind. The Federation rocks!" That was surprisingly simple...</text>
			<crewMember amount="1" class="human"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice req="LIST_CREW_ENGINEER" hidden="true">
		<text>(Engineer Crew) Pretend to be an undercover Rebel spy.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Wooooow, you're a spy? That's soooo cool. I wish I was a spy. Wait, can I be one?! I'd love to help!" They eagerly come aboard, much to the discomfort of your crew. You aren't sure how long this cover story will last, but this person seems oblivious enough that maybe it'll just work out fine.</text>
			<crewMember amount="1" class="human"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice req="REBEL_ID" hidden="true">
		<text>(Fake ID) Pretend to be an undercover Rebel spy.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Wooooow, you're a spy? That's soooo cool. I wish I was a spy. Wait, can I be one?! I'd love to help!" They eagerly come aboard, much to the discomfort of your crew. You aren't sure how long this cover story will last, but this person seems oblivious enough that maybe it'll just work out fine.</text>
			<crewMember amount="1" class="human"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text>Just let them escape.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You aren't going to resort to murdering civilians, no matter the context. Unfortunately, this means the Rebels will only be faster at finding you.</text>
			<modifyPursuit amount="1"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
