<event name="DISTRESS_CRASH_LANDING">
	<text>You arrive at a lonely, starless planet drifting through space. A quick scan of the surface reveals a ship crash landed on the far side of the planet. It's in shambles, but there is a chance someone may have survived.</text>
	<distressBeacon/>
	<img planet="PLANET_UNPOPULATED_SMALL"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Pull closer.</text>
		<event load="CRASH_LANDING_INSPECT"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="sensors" lvl="3">
		<text>(Adv. Sensors) Run a thorough scan.</text>
		<event load="CRASH_LANDING_SCAN"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="ADV_SCANNERS">
		<text>(LRS) Run a thorough scan.</text>
		<event load="CRASH_LANDING_SCAN"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore the planet.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Even if someone did survive, there's not much you could do to help them.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Check the storage.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<eventList name="CRASH_LANDING_INSPECT">
	<event>	
		<text>The ship here is no ordinary vessel. It's a massive Rebel carrier! It must have detected you, because its few remaining systems come online and it dispenses an Auto-ship to face you.</text>
		<ship load="SHIP_AUTO_CRASH_LANDING" hostile="true"/>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Continue...</text>
			<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
		</choice>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>The ship that crashed appears to be a Federation Dreadnaught! There may still be crew alive, but the ship seems to be in a critical state.</text>
		<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CHECK_ANY_CREW" lvl="1" blue="false">
			<text>Try to rescue the crew.</text>
			<event load="CRASH_LANDING_INSPECT_FED_RESCUE"/>
		</choice>
		<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CHECK_ANY_CREW" lvl="0" max_lvl="0" blue="false">
			<text>There's no saviors aboard your vessel to send over.</text>
			<event load="OPTION_INVALID"/>
		</choice>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>It's too late, we should go.</text>
			<event/>
		</choice>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>The ship appears to have once been a Federation carrier, but it's beyond repair. A good section of the hull has collapsed and it's very doubtful anyone survived.</text>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Scrap the ship.</text>
			<event load="CRASH_LANDING_INSPECT_FED_SCRAP"/>
		</choice>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>We aren't pirates, it would be disrespectful to scrap the ship.</text>
			<event/>
		</choice>
	</event>
</eventList>
<eventList name="CRASH_LANDING_SCAN">
	<event>	
		<text>The ship here is no ordinary vessel. It's a massive Rebel carrier! From this distance it hasn't detected you, but several Auto-vessels remain functional inside.</text>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Attack the Auto-ships to access the carrier.</text>
			<event>
				<text>You approach the carrier and prepare for battle.</text>
				<ship load="SHIP_AUTO_CRASH_LANDING" hostile="true"/>
				<choice hidden="true">
					<text>Continue...</text>
					<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Leave the vessel alone.</text>
			<event/>
		</choice>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>The ship appears to have once been a Federation carrier, but it's beyond repair. A good section of the hull has collapsed and it's very doubtful anyone survived, so you make use of the wreckage.</text>
		<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>The ship that crashed appears to be a Federation Dreadnaught! There may still be crew alive, but the ship seems to be in a critical state. With your scans, you make certain you give yourself enough time to escape before a structural collapse, and rush in to collect some of the survivors.</text>
		<crewMember amount="1" class="human"/>
	</event>
</eventList>
<eventList name="CRASH_LANDING_INSPECT_FED_RESCUE">
	<event>
		<text>Your crew returns with a single survivor. It appears the rest of the Federation crew were either killed in the crash or the following inferno.</text>
		<crewMember amount="1" class="human"/>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>You watch in horror as the carrier collapses, no doubt burying your crew inside.</text>
		<removeCrew>
			<clone>true</clone>
			<text>Luckily your crew is already being cloned and is revived a short time later.</text>
		</removeCrew>
	</event>
</eventList>
<eventList name="CRASH_LANDING_INSPECT_FED_SCRAP">
	<event>
		<text>You are uninterrupted as you salvage the carrier.</text>
		<autoReward level="MED">standard</autoReward>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>It appears one of the Federation Auto-ships onboard is still functional! It detects your attempts at salvaging as hostile and attacks.</text>
		<ship load="SHIP_FED_AUTO" hostile="true"/>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Continue...</text>
			<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
		</choice>
	</event>
</eventList>

<event name="DISTRESS_FEDERATION_LOST">
	<text>Despite the distress beacon, no ship is in sight. Quite strange...</text>
	<distressBeacon/>
	<img planet="NONE"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Keep looking.</text>
		<event load="DISTRESS_FEDERATION_LOST_TRACK"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="INFO_MACHINE">
		<text>(Analyzer) Collect the logs of the most recent arrival.</text>
		<event load="DISTRESS_FEDERATION_LOST_LOGS"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Oh well.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You keep on moving with your mission.</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Check the storage.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
