		<text>The data provided by the diagnostics informs you that a Federation vessel last visited this beacon - but their identification seems to have been forged. If there ever was one, this is as clear a sign as can be that a pirate lurks nearby.</text>
		<ship load="SHIP_PIRATE_ALL" hostile="false"/>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Engage the pirate.</text>
			<event>
				<text>You have no difficulty tracking down the pirate thanks to your logs and prepare for combat.</text>
				<ship hostile="true"/>
				<choice hidden="true">
					<text>Continue...</text>
					<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Ignore the pirate.</text>
			<event/>
		</choice>
	</event>
</eventList>

<event name="DISTRESS_ASB_PIRATE" unique="true"> <!--no longer spawns-->
	<text>You arrive at the source of the distress beacon, but find only a pirate! "Now, listen up. See that planet over there? On the surface is a series of active Anti-Ship Battery systems that I am now in control of. I am the only one stopping them from firing on you, and I don't really have a reason to keep doing that... but I think we can make a mutually beneficial deal here..."</text>
	<distressBeacon/>
	<img planet="PLANET_POPULATED_SMALL"/>
	<ship load="SHIP_PIRATE_ALL" hostile="false"/>
	<choice>
		<text>Pay the "fee of protection".</text>
		<event>
			<text>"A wise, wise choice captain. I'll keep those ASBs offline... for now at least..."</text>
			<item_modify>
				<item type="scrap" min="-25" max="-15"/>
			</item_modify>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Refuse to pay.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Tsk tsk. Well, I did warn you..." The pirate wasn't lying - the nearby ASB systems activate immediately and lock onto your location!</text>
			<environment type="PDS" target="player"/>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="PDS_DISABLE">
		<text>(Signal Diluter) Disable his control over the ASB systems.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Wait... wait! What have you done!? God damn it! You have no idea how hard it was to gain access to those! You're gonna pay for this!"</text>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="hacking" lvl="2">
		<text>(Upg. Hacking) Take access of the systems yourself and redirect them onto the pirate.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Tsk tsk. Well, I did warn y-... wait, why are those aiming at me?! What have you done? Crap, you've ruined everything!"</text>
			<environment type="PDS" target="enemy"/>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="slug_saboteur">
		<text>(Saboteur Crew) Take access of the systems yourself and redirect them onto the pirate.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Tsk tsk. Well, I did warn y-... wait, why are those aiming at me?! What have you done? Crap, you've ruined everything!"</text>
			<environment type="PDS" target="enemy"/>
			<ship hostile="true"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="mind" lvl="2">
		<text>(Upg. Mind Control) "Convince" him to keep the ASBs offline.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Mmmm, you make a good point. Tee hee!" The pirate immediately slumps over. Apparently the mind control had some very adverse effects on him. We better get out of here before he wakes up.</text>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

<event name="DISTRESS_MANTIS_IDLE" unique="true">
	<text>At the source of the distress beacon you find an idle Mantis ship with all of its weapons offline. You aren't sure what happened, or what you should do.</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_MANTIS_GENERIC" hostile="false"/>
	<distressBeacon/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Scrap the ship.</text>
		<event load="MANTIS_IDLE_SCRAP"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Hail the ship.</text>
		<event load="MANTIS_IDLE_HAIL"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore the ship.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You're wary of the Mantis but figure it's safe to do something on the ship.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<eventList name="MANTIS_IDLE_SCRAP">
	<event>	
		<text>As you approach the ship to scrap it, the lights flicker on, and the sensors detect boarders. It was a trap!</text>
		<ship hostile="true"/>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Continue...</text>
			<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
		</choice>
		<boarders min="2" max="2" class="mantis"/>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>You're undisturbed as you scrap the ship. Inside you even find an unused augment lying on the ground!</text>
		<autoReward level="MED">augment</autoReward>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>Inside the ship you find signs of a greater conflict. Lacerations on the Hive Mantis suggest the damage was dealt by other fellow Mantis. Your suspicions are affirmed when you find a young Free Mantis locked in the cargo-hold who had fled from the fight. He seems to be eager to join your crew.</text>
		<crewMember amount="1" class="mantis_free"/>
		<autoReward level="LOW">stuff</autoReward>
	</event>
</eventList>
<eventList name="MANTIS_IDLE_HAIL">
	<event>	
		<text>You hail the ship, trying to see if they're still alive. However, their weapons come online in response and they move in to attack!</text>
		<ship hostile="true"/>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Continue...</text>
			<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
		</choice>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>You quickly receive a response, albeit a very rude one. "Eating crap and die, Federation! Not needing help from YOU!" It seems they must have been attacked recently, and their engines aren't functioning.</text>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Retaliate and attack.</text>
			<event>
				<text>With the ship damaged like this, it should be easy to finish it off.</text>
				<status type="limit" target="enemy" system="engines" amount="0"/>
				<ship hostile="true"/>
				<choice hidden="true">
					<text>Continue...</text>
					<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_HIVE">
			<text>(Hive Crew) Hail again.</text>
			<event>
				<text>"Bah, engines are toast. Worthless junk machine. Not needing this right now. Must kill again, soon. Will go with you."</text>
				<crewMember amount="1" class="mantis"/>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice hidden="true" req="LIST_CREW_FREEMAN">
			<text>(Free Mantis Crew) Hail again and taunt the Mantis.</text>
			<event>
				<text>"Free Mantis laughing at me, but them is one who lacking braincell by dozens! I using your spines as soup ladels!"</text>
				<status type="limit" target="enemy" system="engines" amount="0"/>
				<ship hostile="true"/>
				<choice hidden="true">
					<text>Continue...</text>
					<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Leave the ship alone.</text>
			<event/>
		</choice>
	</event>
</eventList>

<event name="DISTRESS_FACTORY" unique="true">
	<text>The source of the distress beacon appears not to be a ship, but a large factory. You can't see anything noticeably wrong, but it is definitely the right location.</text>
	<distressBeacon/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Approach the factory.</text>
		<event>
			<text>Upon further inspection it is clear something is very wrong. A fire has broken out in the factory, and your ship's computers are being overloaded with signals as thousands of distress beacons are activated at once... it's a distress beacon factory!?</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Try to rescue any workers who might be trapped.</text>
				<event load="DISTRESS_FACTORY_RESCUE"/>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" req="PDS_DISABLE">
				<text>(Signal Diluter) Block out the signals and approach.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You feel immediate relief as the barrage of signals comes to an end. With that distraction out of the way, you manage to escort several of the workers onto your ship before you have to pull away to avoid the debris. Though you drop most off nearby, one offers to stay. Probably because it pays better than their old job, if you had to guess.</text>
					<crewMember amount="1" repair="1"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true" req="BLUELIST_CREW_NOFIRE">
				<text>(Fireproof Crew) Send in your crew to rescue the workers.</text>
				<event>
					<text>You might not be able to pull the ship close enough, but you can send your crew over by themselves. Your crew returns back on the shuttle with several other workers unharmed. Though you drop most off nearby, one offers to stay. Probably because it pays better than their old job, if you had to guess.</text>
					<crewMember amount="1" repair="1"/>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Leave now before your ship is consumed by the inferno or your systems stop functioning entirely.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Avoid the factory.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The business of this factory isn't a concern of yours.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<eventList name="DISTRESS_FACTORY_RESCUE">
	<event>
		<text>As you approach the factory, your navigation screen becomes overwhelmed by the number of distress beacons increasing everfold. Unable to maneuver properly, your ship collides with some of the debris and eventually you're forced to pull out before the damage becomes unrecoverable.</text>
		<damage amount="2" effect="breach" system="random"/>
		<damage amount="3"/>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>Though the number of signals continues to increase rapidly, you manage to escort several of the workers onto your ship before you have to pull away. Though you drop most off nearby, one offers to stay. Probably because it pays better than their old job, if you had to guess.</text>
		<crewMember amount="1" repair="1"/>
	</event>
</eventList>

