<event name="QUEST_MERCENARY_DELIVERY_START" unique="true">
	<ship load="SHIP_SMUGGLER_ALL" hostile="false"/>
	<text>You jump to the beacon and discover an Argeonn vessel orbiting the beacon. They hail you with a proposal. "Say, that's a nice ship you got there... But I am sure a bit of scrap could make it run even better. Care to make some quick, easy cash?"</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Express your interest.</text>
		<event load="MERCENARY_DELIVERY_INTEREST"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="FEDERATION_DATABASE">
		<text>[Federation Database] Who is Argeonn?</text>
		<event>
			<text id="database_argeonn"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event>
					<restartEvent/>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>This already sounds shady... move on.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You tell the smuggler you have no interest, and prepare to leave. They don't seem to mind.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="MERCENARY_DELIVERY_INTEREST" unique="true">
	<text>"You see, I am a little short on fuel, but I still have to make a delivery of some... less than legal goods. If you can deliver them to these coordinates, the profits are all yours. Of course, if you have some spare fuel yourself, I'd pay you nicely for it."</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Agree to the delivery.</text>
		<event>
			<text>They transmit the coordinates to your computer and teleport a very suspect-looking crate into your cargo hold. You scan it for explosives, just to be safe, but it's nothing more than Slug narcotics.</text>
			<quest event="QUEST_MERCENARY_DELIVERY_END"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Count us out. We're not smugglers.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Your loss." They immediately activate their cloak, and presumably leave.</text>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice>
		<text>Sell them a bit of your fuel.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You transfer over some fuel to the mercenaries. It's not much, but they seem satisfied, and in return they give you some scrap.</text>
			<item_modify>
				<item type="fuel" min="-3" max="-3"/>
				<item type="scrap" min="10" max="15"/>
			</item_modify>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="QUEST_MERCENARY_DELIVERY_END">
	<text>You arrive at the beacon. There's already a ship there, waiting for you. "So... got the goods?"</text>
	<ship load="QUEST_MERCENARY_DELIVER_SHIP" hostile="false"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Transfer the contraband over.</text>
		<event load="QUEST_MERCENARY_DELIVERY_TRANSFER"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Demand payment first.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Fine, fine." They pass over the payment, and you send over the narcotics. Easy money.</text>
			<autoReward level="LOW">scrap_only</autoReward>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<eventList name="QUEST_MERCENARY_DELIVERY_TRANSFER">
	<event>
		<text>You pass over the drugs, and wait while the other ship looks them over. "Everything seems to be in check... but I don't think we'll be paying."</text>
		<choice hidden="true">
			<text>Raise your weapons and prepare to take the payment from them yourself.</text>
			<event>
			<text>You're not going to let anyone double cross you, especially not some narcotics addicted scum! You point your weapon array towards them.</text>
				<ship hostile="true"/>
				<choice hidden="true">
					<text>Continue...</text>
					<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
				</choice>
			</event>
		</choice>
	</event>
	<event>
		<text>You pass over the drugs, and wait while the other ship looks them over. "Everything seems to be in check... job well done."</text>
		<autoReward level="MED">scrap_only</autoReward>
	</event>
</eventList>

